---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { webPageSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const structuredData = [
  webPageSchema({
    name: 'Mood Changes & Brain Fog in Perimenopause | The Second Spring',
    description: "Anxiety, irritability, low mood, and brain fog during perimenopause are hormonal — not character flaws or stress. Here is what's happening and what helps.",
    url: '/guide/mood-memory',
  }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Guide', url: '/guide' },
    { name: 'Mood & Brain Fog', url: '/guide/mood-memory' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title="Mood Changes & Brain Fog in Perimenopause | The Second Spring"
  description="Anxiety, irritability, low mood, and brain fog during perimenopause are hormonal — not character flaws or stress. Here is what's happening and what helps."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="ig-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-hero-inner">
        <div class="ig-eyebrow">🧠 Topic Guide</div>
        <h1>Mood & Memory in Perimenopause</h1>
        <p>Anxiety, brain fog, and mood swings are among the most distressing perimenopausal symptoms — and among the most misunderstood, especially in India.</p>
        <div class="ig-share-row">
          <span class="ig-share-label">Share this guide</span>
          <a href="https://wa.me/?text=Why perimenopause affects mood and memory — and what helps — https://thesecondspring.org/guide/mood-memory" target="_blank" class="ig-share-btn ig-wa">WhatsApp</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 01 — THE BRAIN-HORMONE CONNECTION -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">01 / Why Hormones Affect Your Mind</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">Oestrogen and progesterone directly regulate brain chemistry</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">This is not in your head — it is in your hormones. The same messengers that regulate your cycle also govern your neurotransmitters, your stress response, and your memory.</p>

      <div class="brain-grid">
        <div class="brain-card brain-card--oestrogen">
          <div class="brain-icon">🌸</div>
          <h3 class="brain-name">Oestrogen & the brain</h3>
          <ul class="brain-list">
            <li>Modulates serotonin, dopamine, and noradrenaline — the neurotransmitters that regulate mood, motivation, and emotional resilience</li>
            <li>Supports blood flow to the brain and protects neurons</li>
            <li>When oestrogen fluctuates erratically, so do these neurotransmitters — producing mood swings and emotional reactivity</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="brain-what-happens">
            <div class="bwh-label">What happens in perimenopause</div>
            <div class="bwh-desc">Erratic oestrogen surges and drops make mood and emotional regulation unpredictable. Good days and bad days follow the hormonal rollercoaster.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="brain-card brain-card--progesterone">
          <div class="brain-icon">🌿</div>
          <h3 class="brain-name">Progesterone & calm</h3>
          <ul class="brain-list">
            <li>Metabolises into allopregnanolone — a natural anti-anxiety compound that acts on GABA receptors</li>
            <li>Its decline in perimenopause removes a key calming buffer from the nervous system</li>
            <li>Poor sleep (itself hormonal) amplifies ALL mood and cognitive symptoms significantly</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="brain-what-happens">
            <div class="bwh-label">What happens in perimenopause</div>
            <div class="bwh-desc">Progesterone falls early and fast — before oestrogen. The brain becomes more reactive to stress, producing anxiety, mood swings, and cognitive slowing.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ig-callout">
        <span class="ig-callout-icon">🇮🇳</span>
        <span>In India, perimenopausal anxiety and mood changes are frequently misattributed to family stress, relationship issues, or "personality." This delays diagnosis and treatment by <strong>years</strong>. You deserve a hormonal assessment first.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 02 — WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">02 / Symptoms</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">The mood and cognitive symptoms of perimenopause</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">These symptoms are distinct from clinical mental illness — though they can overlap. Their hormonal origin means they respond differently to treatment.</p>

      <div class="symptom-grid">
        <div class="symptom-card">
          <div class="symptom-icon">😤</div>
          <h3 class="symptom-title">Mood swings & irritability</h3>
          <p class="symptom-desc">Sudden waves of frustration or tearfulness that feel out of proportion to the trigger. These correlate directly with hormonal fluctuation — particularly drops in oestrogen.</p>
          <a href="/guide/symptoms/mood-swings" class="symptom-link">Mood swings guide →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="symptom-card">
          <div class="symptom-icon">😰</div>
          <h3 class="symptom-title">Anxiety</h3>
          <p class="symptom-desc">New-onset anxiety in your 40s with no prior history is a classic perimenopausal presentation. Can include first-ever panic attacks. Often dismissed as "stress" for years.</p>
          <a href="/guide/symptoms/anxiety" class="symptom-link">Anxiety guide →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="symptom-card">
          <div class="symptom-icon">🌧️</div>
          <h3 class="symptom-title">Low mood</h3>
          <p class="symptom-desc">Persistent flatness, loss of interest, reduced motivation — distinct from clinical depression but often overlapping. Frequently treated with antidepressants when the root cause is hormonal.</p>
          <a href="/guide/symptoms/low-mood" class="symptom-link">Low mood guide →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="symptom-card">
          <div class="symptom-icon">🌫️</div>
          <h3 class="symptom-title">Brain fog</h3>
          <p class="symptom-desc">Forgetting words mid-sentence, losing train of thought, difficulty concentrating, slow processing. Hormonally driven and typically temporary — though it can feel alarming.</p>
          <a href="/guide/symptoms/brain-fog" class="symptom-link">Brain fog guide →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 03 — WHAT HELPS -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">03 / Evidence-Based Approaches</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">What works for mood and memory during perimenopause</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">A combination of hormonal, psychological, and lifestyle approaches produces the best outcomes. The right starting point depends on your specific pattern of symptoms.</p>

      <div class="helps-grid">
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--medical">🩺 Medical</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>HRT</strong> — addresses the root hormonal cause; often the most effective intervention</li>
            <li><strong>Micronised progesterone</strong> — calming effect on GABA receptors; particularly helpful for anxiety</li>
            <li><strong>SSRIs / SNRIs</strong> — evidence for both hot flash reduction and mood stabilisation</li>
            <li><strong>CBT (cognitive behavioural therapy)</strong> — highly effective for perimenopausal anxiety and mood, particularly when combined with hormonal treatment</li>
            <li><strong>Psychiatric referral</strong> — appropriate if symptoms are severe, or if there is overlap with clinical depression</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--lifestyle">🌿 Lifestyle</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>Regular aerobic exercise</strong> — equivalent to a mild antidepressant in clinical studies</li>
            <li><strong>Strength training</strong> — additional mood and energy benefits beyond aerobic exercise</li>
            <li><strong>Reducing alcohol and caffeine</strong> — both worsen anxiety and sleep</li>
            <li><strong>Sleep prioritisation</strong> — poor sleep amplifies every mood and cognitive symptom</li>
            <li><strong>Mindfulness and yoga nidra</strong> — evidence for anxiety and cortisol reduction specifically</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--support">💬 Support</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>iCall helpline</strong> — 9152987821 (Mon–Sat, 8am–10pm) — low-cost or free mental health support — check their website for current fee structure</li>
            <li><strong>The Second Spring companion</strong> — private support any time, India-specific</li>
            <li><strong>Not carrying this alone</strong> — isolation significantly worsens anxiety and mood. Connection matters.</li>
            <li><strong>Emergency</strong> — call 112 in India</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 04 — INDIA CONTEXT -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">04 / The Indian Picture</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">Why mood symptoms go unrecognised in Indian women</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">The combination of cultural stigma and hormonal ignorance means Indian women routinely spend years seeking help before receiving a useful answer.</p>

      <div class="india-grid">
        <div class="india-card">
          <div class="india-icon">🔇</div>
          <h3 class="india-title">Mental health stigma</h3>
          <p class="india-desc">Seeking help for anxiety or low mood is still widely seen as weakness in many Indian households. Women suffer silently for years rather than asking for support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="india-card">
          <div class="india-icon">🧓</div>
          <h3 class="india-title">Dismissed as ageing</h3>
          <p class="india-desc">Symptoms are culturally dismissed as "just getting old" or "what all women go through." The hormonal cause — and the treatability of that cause — is rarely acknowledged.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="india-card">
          <div class="india-icon">💊</div>
          <h3 class="india-title">Antidepressants without hormone testing</h3>
          <p class="india-desc">Doctors frequently prescribe antidepressants or anxiolytics without considering or testing for a hormonal cause — leaving the root issue entirely unaddressed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ig-callout">
        <span class="ig-callout-icon">💡</span>
        <span>You deserve a proper hormonal assessment — FSH, E2, progesterone, and thyroid — <strong>before</strong> being told it is "just anxiety" or "just stress." These tests are inexpensive and widely available in India.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="ig-cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-cta-inner">
        <div class="ig-cta-left">
          <h2>Could your mood changes be hormonal?</h2>
          <p>Our free symptom check helps you understand what is driving what you are feeling — and what to ask your gynaecologist. Built specifically for Indian women.</p>
          <div class="ig-cta-btns">
            <a href="/quiz" class="btn btn-peach btn-lg">Check My Symptoms →</a>
            <a href="/chat" class="btn btn-outline-white">Talk Privately</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ig-cta-stat-col">
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">40s</span><span class="ig-stat-label">New-onset anxiety in your 40s is a classic perimenopausal presentation — not a personal failing</span></div>
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">Years</span><span class="ig-stat-label">Average time Indian women wait before their mood symptoms are correctly attributed to hormones</span></div>
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">9152987821</span><span class="ig-stat-label">iCall — low-cost or free mental health support, Mon–Sat 8am–10pm — check their website for current fee structure</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* HERO */
  .ig-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0F2A1A 0%, #1A3D2B 60%, #2A5C45 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ig-hero-inner { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .ig-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: rgba(255,255,255,.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); color: rgba(255,255,255,.85); font-size: .78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .4rem 1rem; border-radius: 100px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .ig-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.03em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ig-hero p { font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.75); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .ig-share-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .ig-share-label { font-size: .85rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.55); }
  .ig-share-btn { font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 700; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 99px; text-decoration: none; }
  .ig-wa { background: #25D366; color: #fff; }

  /* SECTIONS */
  .ig-section { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .bg-white { background: #fff; }
  .bg-cream { background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); }
  .ig-card-label { font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); background: var(--green-light, #E8F0EB); display: inline-block; padding: .3rem .9rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ig-card-label.center { display: block; text-align: center; }
  .ig-section-title { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.025em; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .75rem; text-align: center; }
  .ig-section-sub { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.7; text-align: center; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; }

  /* CALLOUT */
  .ig-callout { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; background: var(--green-light, #E8F0EB); border-left: 4px solid var(--green, #1A3D2B); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.65; }
  .ig-callout--peach { background: #FEF3EC; border-color: #D4845A; }
  .ig-callout-icon { font-size: 1.3rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* BRAIN HORMONE CARDS */
  .brain-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .brain-card { border-radius: 20px; padding: 2rem; }
  .brain-card--oestrogen { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FEF3EC, #FDDCC8); border: 2px solid #D4845A; }
  .brain-card--progesterone { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #E8F0EB, #C8DDD0); border: 2px solid var(--green, #1A3D2B); }
  .brain-icon { font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .brain-name { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .brain-card--oestrogen .brain-name { color: #9D4E1E; }
  .brain-card--progesterone .brain-name { color: #1A3D2B; }
  .brain-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding: 0; }
  .brain-list li { font-size: .875rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; position: relative; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.6; }
  .brain-list li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .brain-card--oestrogen .brain-list li::before { color: #D4845A; }
  .brain-card--progesterone .brain-list li::before { color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); }
  .brain-what-happens { border-radius: 10px; padding: .85rem 1rem; }
  .brain-card--oestrogen .brain-what-happens { background: rgba(212,132,90,.12); }
  .brain-card--progesterone .brain-what-happens { background: rgba(26,61,43,.1); }
  .bwh-label { font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; margin-bottom: .35rem; }
  .brain-card--oestrogen .bwh-label { color: #9D4E1E; }
  .brain-card--progesterone .bwh-label { color: #1A3D2B; }
  .bwh-desc { font-size: .85rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* SYMPTOM CARDS */
  .symptom-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .symptom-card { background: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .symptom-icon { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .symptom-title { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .4rem; }
  .symptom-desc { font-size: .875rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 1rem; flex: 1; }
  .symptom-link { font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); text-decoration: underline; margin-top: auto; }
  .symptom-link:hover { color: #2A5C45; }

  /* HELPS */
  .helps-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .helps-col { background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .helps-head { font-size: .9rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: .75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid; }
  .helps-head--medical { border-color: #D4845A; color: #9D4E1E; }
  .helps-head--lifestyle { border-color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); }
  .helps-head--support { border-color: #7FB89A; color: #2A5C45; }
  .helps-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .helps-list li { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.55; padding-left: 1rem; position: relative; }
  .helps-list li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); font-size: .75rem; }

  /* INDIA GRID */
  .india-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .india-card { background: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); }
  .india-icon { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .india-title { font-size: .97rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .4rem; }
  .india-desc { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.65; }

  /* CTA */
  .ig-cta-section { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0F2A1A, #1A3D2B); padding: 5rem 0; color: #fff; }
  .ig-cta-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: center; }
  .ig-cta-left h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.03em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .ig-cta-left p { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.75); margin-bottom: 1.75rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .ig-cta-btns { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-peach { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; padding: .75rem 1.5rem; background: #D4845A; color: #fff; border-radius: 99px; font-weight: 700; font-size: .9rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all .18s; }
  .btn-peach:hover { background: #bf7249; }
  .btn-lg { padding: .85rem 1.75rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .btn-outline-white { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; padding: .75rem 1.5rem; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.4); color: #fff; border-radius: 99px; font-weight: 700; font-size: .9rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all .18s; }
  .btn-outline-white:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,.1); }
  .ig-cta-stat-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .ig-stat { background: rgba(255,255,255,.07); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12); border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .25rem; }
  .ig-stat-num { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 900; color: #FBBF81; letter-spacing: -.03em; }
  .ig-stat-label { font-size: .83rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.7); line-height: 1.4; }

  /* RESPONSIVE */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .brain-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .symptom-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .helps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .india-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .ig-cta-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .india-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ig-cta-btns { flex-direction: column; }
  }
</style>
